The Kentucky Traumatic Brain Injury Trust Fund Board is hereby created for the purpose of administering the trust fund. The board shall be composed of nine (9) members including the secretary of the Cabinet for Health and Family Services or the secretary's designee, the executive director of the Brain Injury Association of Kentucky or the executive director's designee, the state medical epidemiologist, and the following members, to be appointed by the Governor:
One (1) member shall be a neurosurgeon;
One (1) member shall be a neuropsychologist or psychiatrist;
One (1) member shall be a rehabilitation specialist;
One (1) member shall be a social worker experienced in working with brain-injured individuals; and
Two (2) members shall be family members of or individuals with a brain injury.
